"use strict";(self.webpackChunkwebpage=self.webpackChunkwebpage||[]).push([[851],{9851:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"menu":{"company":"company","team":"team","rule":"rule","contact":"contact us","home":"home"},"s1-title1":"Free is by no means the most expensive","s1-title2":"We solemnly state: There is no commercial routine!","s1-title3":"Let there be no hot potatoes in the world, and let civilians have the tools to take advantage of it.","s1-title4":"Internet of Everything — Delivering Solutions","s1-title5":"You handle the procurement of the equipment yourself. We do not take charge of this process; our aim is to ensure openness and transparency, and we do not intervene as intermediaries.","company":{"name":"Guang Zhou Workers Rat Race on the Internet technology COM. LTD","address":"303 Rm. 303 Hua Ying Shang Sha Bulding ,East Zhong Shan Ave No. 280-1, HuangPu Dist,Guang Zhou ,Guang Dong","description":"Hello, my name is Tang Lin, a software developer who has been cast aside by the corporate world. I took the lead in establishing *Guangzhou \\"Workplace Outcasts\\" Internet Technology Co., Ltd.*—a newly founded enterprise brimming with vitality and grit. Our internal staff consists entirely of seasoned, mature-age technical professionals who, like me, were marginalized by the traditional corporate environment; collectively, we possess an average of five years of industry experience. These individuals are colleagues and friends I have known throughout my career—people who, just like me, faced exclusion within the workplace. Even while still employed in the corporate sector, I harbored a persistent desire to start my own company; thus, its establishment was an inevitable outcome. I admit I was somewhat unconventional when choosing the company\'s name; I had previously considered options like \\"Private Customization\\" or \\"Enterprise Customization,\\" but I felt those titles failed to capture the personal backstory and journey behind the venture. Instead, I believe our current name—\\"Workplace Outcasts\\"—frankly and clearly articulates my current circumstances and the mission I aim to fulfill at this stage. The decision to adopt this specific operational model was largely driven by the prevailing trends and momentum of the modern internet landscape. We are a diligent and hardworking team with a passion for continuous learning and research. We also love sharing the fruits of our research with the public, offering a wide array of tools and services completely free of charge. We aspire to stand at the vanguard of technology, exploring new frontiers and shouldering the inherent risks of innovation on your behalf. I pledge to do everything within my power to support and nurture every entrepreneur who possesses the courage to pursue their dreams. Our company offers free custom development services for business systems—including ERP, CMS, and OA—as well as Mini Programs, mobile apps, and 2D casual games. Our scope covers internet-based software products for both PC and mobile platforms (excluding hardware for the time being), as well as application development in cutting-edge technological fields such as IoT, AI, OCR, VR/AR, RVC, and WebRTC. Should the opportunity arise in the future, our company intends to expand into business areas that integrate both hardware and software solutions tailored for \\"private and enterprise customization\\"—this constitutes the grand strategic objective guiding our forward trajectory. We sincerely hope that you will enjoy our products and services, just as we take immense pleasure in dedicating ourselves to crafting effective, practical tools for professionals across a diverse range of industries."},"rule":{"contents":"Page Contents","p1":{"title":"A Word Up Front","p11":"Open Source - All tools adhere to the GPL open-source license.","p12":"Freedom—freedom is not doing whatever you want; rather, freedom is having the autonomous choice not to do what you do not wish to do.","p13":"Fairness — If the temple is small, we engage in no malicious competition and commit no acts that benefit ourselves at the expense of others; if the temple is large, we do not monopolize.","p14":"Transparency — Financial inflows and outflows are fully transparent and open to public scrutiny. We provide services in black and white—clear, explicit, and documented—eschewing underhanded tactics and linguistic trickery.","p15":"We spare no effort to support every entrepreneur or any dreamer."},"p2":{"title":"reveal industry peers","p21":"In this section, our company outlines our rules and regulations; should any omissions or oversights be identified, they will be thoroughly and comprehensively addressed and incorporated herein. Additionally, we take this opportunity to expose certain industry insider secrets—specifically, common commercial \\"free\\" traps:","p22":{"p221":"<strong>Harvesting users under the guise of being free.</strong>，Products of this nature are either riddled with incessant advertisements or require payment for access to additional tools. A common example can be found in certain major games and applications: while they do indeed allow you to download and play them for free, they deliberately hinder your gameplay—preventing a smooth, enjoyable experience—until you voluntarily spend money to purchase in-game items or tools. The underlying logic is simple: buying something feels good in the moment, and continuing to buy ensures that good feeling lasts. In short, it boils down to this:<strong>\\"Free is the most expensive.\\"</strong>。","p222":{"p2221":"<strong>Offered under the guise of being free, but with ulterior motives.</strong>\\"Free\\" is often merely a smokescreen; the true objective lies elsewhere. A common example involves certain \\"free\\" apps: while they appear to be free on the surface, their actual purpose may be to harvest user data, promote other paid services, or even engage in malicious marketing activities.","p2222":"Services that are essentially free trials—such as those requiring renewal upon expiration—are generally considered quite normal (similar to Point 3).","p2223":"Fundamentally, this constitutes fraud: the product offered for free does not match the product actually being promoted, even though the two are related—a common example being vocational or job-specific training.","p2224":"Fundamentally, it is a form of exchange: offering something for free in return for a foothold in the market. (Malicious enterprises, however, may trade this for your personal privacy or other commercial data, which they then repurpose for other ends.) In the industry, this practice is referred to as *juan*—intense, cutthroat competition.","p2225":"Fundamentally, it is an act of sabotage—wreaking havoc under the guise of offering something for free in order to achieve one\'s own ends. Take cracked software, for instance: the patch used to bypass its security measures may contain scripts capable of damaging your system or infiltrating your personal computer to access and read your data."},"p223":"This style of marketing—reminiscent of a \\"sticky plaster\\" that clings relentlessly—involves revealing only half of the business operations while concealing the other. It engages in aggressive promotion to gain a competitive edge, selectively highlighting only those aspects that resonate with the emotional sentiments of users. While the claim of \\"free\\" is indeed technically true, the offering requires additional components to constitute a complete, functional product—and these supplementary components come with a fee. A common example of this is a product that is genuinely open-source, yet charges for its documentation."}},"p3":{"title":"Why Are We Free?","p31":"We, too, must secure a foothold in the market; this form of intense competition we term \\"Upward Competition.\\" In contrast to \\"Downward Competition\\"—which refers to the unprincipled, rock-bottom pricing strategies and labor exploitation practiced by unscrupulous merchants—\\"Upward Competition\\" drives social progress by fostering innovation and generating new employment opportunities. It serves to boost productive efficiency and phase out traditional operational methods. One could go so far as to say that we are orchestrating a revolution.","p32":"In essence, we serve as your technical shareholders; our purest objective is to provide every entrepreneur with the production tools necessary to successfully bring their venture to fruition.","p33":"In the context of internet commercialization, the inherent value of software tools varies significantly; if you price them too high, you are essentially operating as an outsourcing service provider; if you price them too low, you are merely a commercial software vendor. However, given the current economic climate, the consumer market is evidently unwilling to pay even the bare development cost for a commercial tool or software system. Consequently, a tool demonstrates its true value only when it serves a broader product ecosystem. Software licensed via registration keys represents a value proposition focused on solving a specific, singular problem. Since such software can be replicated and distributed in multiple copies, pricing it strictly at the developer\'s cost is clearly an untenable strategy; ultimately, sales volume depends entirely on sales capabilities and market acceptance.","p34":"Minimize corporate expenditures on technical personnel, thereby eliminating—at the source—wasteful human resource practices, such as employee slacking.","p35":"Engage and support seasoned, mature job seekers who have been cast aside by the market; explore innovative employment models tailored to current national realities and economic trends; re-empower the act of hiring and redefine the nature of work; and ultimately cultivate a near-perfect ecosystem for independent professionals.","p36":"Maximize the value contributed by each individual member to society.","p37":"Committed to Optimal Solutions: Unlike the traditional outsourcing industry, we tailor our approach—and allocate the corresponding personnel—based on your specific budget and the project\'s profitability. We strictly reject \\"fast-food\\" style projects—by which we mean a rushed approach where the sole objective is to secure client sign-off for the sake of profit, without regard for the critical integration between the product itself and its operational strategy. Our sole aim is to provide our clients with the truly optimal solution."},"p4":{"title":"Operating Model","p41":"Project operations proceed through the following three relationships:","p42":{"title":"Three Types of Relationships","p421":{"title":"一、Copartnership","p4211":"As the name implies, this arrangement involves a mutually beneficial cooperation in which both parties share joint responsibility for the project. We will align with your specific concepts and requirements to provide—at no labor cost to you—a fully customized version of your tool or product. It is important to note that under this model, our team begins to receive a revenue share only after your project starts generating income. Furthermore, our team encompasses a comprehensive range of roles—including Product Management, UI/UX Design, QA Testing, Development, and Operations—ensuring that all your needs are promptly addressed. Consequently, prior to formally commencing work, our team may offer constructive suggestions based on our professional expertise. This collaborative cooperation offers two distinct options for clients to choose from:","p4212":{"title":"Mode 1: Cost Cap","p42121":"We will recoup only twice our direct personnel costs. These costs will be calculated based on the rates defined in the <a1>Tier 1</a1> category of our \\"Employment-Based Pricing\\" structure. Based on the specifics of your project, we will establish a specific financial range (defined by a minimum and maximum threshold); within this range, you will designate a specific profit-sharing percentage to be allocated to us (effectively serving as a flexible installment plan—naturally, this percentage represents a share of your total revenue). During this period, we will not interfere with your operational management of the project, and this arrangement will remain in effect until our costs have been fully recouped. In any given month where revenue is zero or the project incurs a net loss, we will not participate in profit-sharing; however, the profit-sharing percentage may be adjusted in the subsequent month. Once our costs have been fully recouped (and the contract has consequently terminated), should you require the development of new features or ongoing maintenance services, new features will be billed according to <a2>Tier 2</a2> rates, while maintenance services will be billed according to <a3>Tier 3</a3> rates (please refer to the \\"Employment-Based Pricing\\" section below). Contract termination may occur in one of two ways: \\"Natural Termination\\"—occurring automatically once our required costs have been fully recouped; or \\"Forced Termination\\"—triggered by events such as corporate bankruptcy and liquidation, or the startup team\'s decision to abandon the project. In the event of any termination other than \\"Natural Termination,\\" the client party shall not retain ownership of the product\'s assets, resources, or intellectual property rights (including copyrights)."},"p4213":{"title":"Mode 2: Expiration Cap","p42131":"Based on the Project Contribution Value (see the definition below—we anticipate you might ask!), we will collect a fixed monthly fee (via fixed installments; this operates as an assessment-based model, wherein our total revenue may ultimately exceed or fall short of our actual costs, with all financial terms strictly governed by the mutually agreed-upon contract) until the expiration of the contract term. In the event of a non-natural termination of the contract, a liquidation value will be charged in proportion to the Project Contribution Value. As with Mode 1, the client party involved in a non-natural termination shall not retain any rights to the product resources or copyrights."},"p4214":"During the operational period under either of these two models, we will not charge you any additional maintenance fees; this service will remain completely free of charge throughout the entire duration. Furthermore, should you wish to add new features during this period, we will implement them for you free of charge as well, with the only associated cost being the actual expenses incurred (representing an incremental addition to the existing foundation).","p4215":"If you feel you have a confidence level of 80% or higher regarding the project—that is, a high probability of successfully bringing the venture to fruition—we recommend opting for the second plan. Conversely, if you are a startup, currently seeking funding, or considering bringing on a business partner, we suggest choosing the first plan.","p4216":"If you are particularly concerned about resources remaining with a third party—or if you need to safeguard client assets and sensitive data—we recommend utilizing Mode 2 with a shortened retention period, or adopting the \\"Employment Relationship\\" approach described below."},"p422":{"title":"二、Partnership","p4221":"If your project is exceptional—and, coincidentally, you also hold me personally in high regard—then, provided it is feasible, I (and potentially my entire team) would be open to joining you as partners. This represents the most comprehensive approach to providing our services at no cost; specifically, we would contribute our expertise as an equity stake. If your high-quality project requires the continuous development of novel tools and ongoing iterative upgrades, or if your innovative venture is pushing the boundaries at the industry\'s cutting edge, then a true partnership is undoubtedly the optimal solution. As this collaborative model entails striving toward a shared objective, the specific terms would naturally require further discussion."},"p423":{"title":"三、Employment Relationship","p4231":"This system operates on a time-based model, applicable to both part-time and full-time engagements. There are no restrictions on the work location; delivery standards are based solely on deadlines and quality. Work is calculated on the basis that every 8 working hours constitute one full workday. Furthermore, each team member sets their own transparent, fixed hourly rate based on their specific level of industry experience. Under this model, there are three distinct pricing tiers:","p4232":"Tier 1: The actual market rate of each individual team member. (The average rate for team members is $60–$75 per hour; please contact me directly for detailed profiles of the team members.)","p4233":"Tier 2: An 8.5% discount off Tier 1 rates.","p4234":"Tier 3: A 2.5 discount on Tier 1.","p4235":"Note: In both cooperative and partnership arrangements, we will share the risks with you. The cooperative model aligns more closely with our strategic positioning; consequently, under this model, we do not accept every project submitted to us. The final right of interpretation rests with the members of the Private Enterprise Customization Project Team.","p4236":"Regarding employment relationships, please distinguish between \\"outsourcing\\" and \\"labor dispatch.\\" While there is no significant difference in pricing (<a1>Pricing Calculator</a1>), there are distinct differences in the actual mode of employment. Outsourcing constitutes a project-based cooperative relationship, whereas labor dispatch constitutes a human-resource-based cooperative relationship. The former is better suited for clients with clearly defined project requirements, while the latter is better suited for clients with ongoing staffing needs."}}},"p5":{"title":"FAQs","p51":"How do you know the revenue status of my project—specifically, when it became profitable and how much profit it generated?","p52":"Operations are handled on your end, while the data center resides on ours; we will conduct evaluations based on the data, rendering a review of financial statements entirely unnecessary. Furthermore, should the startup team decide to abandon the project, the server resources will remain under our control, so there is no need for concern.","p53":"How can we ensure mutual integrity?","p54":"Both parties are required to participate in the project evaluation and the assessment of output value. The credibility of the evaluation is of no concern to either party, as both will be involved in the oversight process; in other words, the governing framework is established jointly, and the associated risks are shared equally. Regarding project resources—such as source code, servers, and various hardware devices—we require that we initially provide these to you at no cost; full administrative access and control will be formally transferred to you upon the termination of the contract.","p55":"What is Project Contribution Value?","p56":"The \\"Project Contribution Value\\" is expressed as a percentage; this is because the customized project developed for you may constitute merely one component—or perhaps just the tip of the iceberg—within your broader operations. Its calculation formula is as follows: Project Contribution Value = Profit Generated by This Project / Total Company Profit × 100%. Naturally, the specific figure for \\"Profit Generated by This Project\\" is to be assessed by you personally. While we are not concerned if this figure happens to be quite small, please note that under \\"Cooperation Model 2,\\" we will establish a fixed timeframe for the partnership; therefore, we encourage you to strive for the most accurate assessment possible.","p57":"How should a startup team handle the premature termination—or abandonment—of a project?","p58":"Pursuant to this Agreement, should Party A\'s project team unilaterally decide to abandon the project due to internal reasons, compensation shall be provided based on the volume of work completed to date, calculated according to an employment-based model; termination for any other reasons shall not require compensation.","p59":"For any other questions, please contact us; we will respond to you as soon as possible!"},"p6":{"title":"Conclusion","p61":"This is a purely supportive arrangement; I participate in the project (incubation) solely as an advisor—not as a technical partner—and receive no fixed salary. My compensation is derived solely from the final product\'s revenue; consequently, if the client\'s project falls through, I receive nothing (thereby sharing the risk). This model is ideal for early-stage entrepreneurs facing a significant disparity between their project\'s estimated cost and market expectations, particularly those with limited capital whose founders prefer not to allocate a co-founder equity stake to the technical lead (CTO) position. Once the product has successfully launched and entered live operations, one of the following two options is to be selected:","p62":"Cost Cap (Flexible Installments)","p63":"Once the product goes live, a portion of the revenue will be collected on a proportional basis. If revenue performance is strong, the outstanding balance may be settled early. The specific percentage to be allocated should be determined by you, based on your project\'s profitability and cost structure; however, allocating a mere 0.0001% against a revenue of 10,000 is clearly unreasonable. After all, the interest rate offered is an exceptionally fair monthly rate of 0.25% (lower than that of any commercial bank on the market!) and is calculated on a simple interest basis (no fine print tricks, no hidden traps). Cost Formula: Hourly Rate × Project Duration × Interest Rate × 2. Until the balance is fully settled, you are prohibited from changing the name of the collaborating enterprise or individual entity, as well as from changing the registered mobile number or the legal representative. There are two methods for contract termination: \\"Natural Termination,\\" which occurs upon the fulfillment of the contract\'s exit conditions; and \\"Forced Termination,\\" which occurs in the event of corporate bankruptcy and liquidation, or should the entrepreneurial team abandon the project. In cases of termination other than Natural Termination, the client party shall not retain any rights to the product resources or copyrights. The agreement remains in effect until the specified term concludes (fixed-installment plan).","p64":"Expiration Cap (Fixed Installments)","p65":"In this evaluation model, Party A assesses the project\'s profitability based on the inherent value of the product itself. A fixed duration—typically ranging from 2 to 5 years (rather than an unreasonable 20 to 70 years)—is established for monthly profit-sharing. Party B independently calculates the monthly profit-share amount based on the formula: hourly rate × project duration. This model is adopted only if the profit-share figures estimated by both parties are in substantial agreement. Unlike the \\"Cost Recovery\\" model described above, this approach mandates fixed profit-sharing payments until the predetermined duration expires, regardless of whether the project generates a profit—provided, of course, that the project has not been abandoned. However, similar to the \\"Cost Recovery\\" model, there are two scenarios for contract termination: \\"natural termination,\\" which occurs upon the fulfillment of the contract\'s exit conditions; and \\"forced termination,\\" which results from corporate bankruptcy and liquidation or the startup team\'s abandonment of the project. In the event of any termination other than a natural termination, the client party shall not be entitled to the product\'s assets or copyrights.","p66":"However, if the project is perceived as highly likely to fall through—or merely a half-baked, aimless endeavor—the vendor will, in all likelihood, decline to take it on, as they stand to incur losses themselves. Consequently, both of these approaches require the vendor to gain a thorough understanding of the project, immerse themselves deeply within it, and participate fully throughout the entire process—including workshops, research, project facilitation, and active involvement in project meetings and voting.","p67":"Both approaches involve first building and launching the product—getting operations up and running—with the entrepreneur taking immediate action. Execution takes precedence; any issues that arise are addressed as they occur."}},"cal":{"title":"Quote Calculator","p1":"Visible UI","p2":"Total Number of Pages","p21":"Invisible Features","p22":"Project functional points that are not manifested in the UI typically consist of backend functionalities or frontend logic that do not have a visible interface—such as SDK development or build processes.","p23":"Is testing required?","p24":"If you need to ensure that the delivered product has few or no bugs, it is recommended to check this option.","p25":"Is it necessary Sync the front end and back end?","p26":"If no backend business scenarios are involved—or if backend components are present but do not require integration—please do not select this option.","p27":"Number of Architectures","p28":"Architecture serves as the \\"foundation\\" of an entire project. A complete project possesses at least one architecture—a concept that can be broadly understood as a \\"framework.\\" If the project utilizes an existing open-source framework without requiring any custom secondary development, this option need not be selected. If a project entails multi-platform development where each platform is built using a native development approach, the project is considered to have a corresponding number of distinct architectures. Conversely, if multi-platform development is executed using a cross-platform solution (where a single codebase runs across multiple platforms), the entire undertaking is counted as constituting a single architecture.","p29":"Staffs of Developer","p210":"The number of personnel assigned to work on this project; a minimum of one person is required to carry out the work.","p211":"Payment Methods","p212":"please select","p213":"The concept of \\"installments\\" refers to a pricing structure that incorporates specific discounts. The three figures represent three distinct stages of the project: payments are made proportionally following the signing of the contract, the completion of project development, and the final delivery and acceptance. Each installment stage qualifies for a different discounted price.","p214":"Project Duration Assessment","p215":"day","p216":"Calculation Results:","p217":"Start Calculation","hint1":"fill quantity with number here.","hint2":"The calculated results are estimates; actual figures may vary. Please refer to the contract for specific details.","resutlHint":"Note: Time units are in hours (h), and price units are in RMB (CNY). The \'?\' symbol indicates a missing requirement. The associated workload is an estimate. The \'-\' symbol indicates that this feature consists solely of business logic and is not reflected in the UI. The \'x\' symbol indicates that the business logic in this section is independent of the backend (requiring no time allocation)."}}')}}]);